<item>
            <title>[DERBY-6044] Fix poor word breaking in table on download page(s)</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-6044</link>
                <project id="10594" key="DERBY">Derby</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;On the Derby release download page(s) there is a table containing JIRA issue ids and descriptions. Because some of the descriptions are very long, mostly because they contain long test names with no natural point for a break, some browsers break up &quot;DERBY-XXXX&quot; at the hyphen. This makes the page much harder to read, and should be addressed.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
